EXPERIMENTAL
MODEL
TECHNIQUES
AND
EQUIPMENT
FOR
FLUTTER
INVESTIGATIONS
AN
OUTLINE
IS
GIVEN
OF
THE
USES
OF
FLUTTER
MODELS
AS
AN
AID
TO
THE
DESIGNER
IN
THE
AVOIDANCE
OF
FLUTTER
DETAILS
ARE
GIVEN
OF
THE
DIFFERENT
TYPES
AND
METHODS
OF
CONSTRUCTION
THAT
ARE
USED
FOR
FLUTTER
MODELS
AND
OF
THE
VARIOUS
TEST
FACILITIES
THAT
ARE
AVAILABLE
FOR
HIGH
SPEED
AND
LOW
SPEED
TESTS
THE
PROCEDURE
FOLLOWED
IN
THE
UK
FOR
FLUTTER
CLEARANCE
OF
THE
FULL
SCALE
AIRCRAFT
IS
DESCRIBED
AND
THE
VALUE
OF
THE
ELECTRONIC
FLUTTER
